Install ubuntu
open terminal
and do all this 
ðŸ”¹ STEP 1: Update your system

Open a terminal and run:

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

ðŸ”¹ STEP 2: Set up locale (important for ROS)
sudo apt install locales
sudo locale-gen en_US en_US.UTF-8
sudo update-locale LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8 LANG=en_US.UTF-8
export LANG=en_US.UTF-8

ðŸ”¹ STEP 3: Add ROS 2 repository
sudo apt install software-properties-common
sudo add-apt-repository universe

Add the ROS key:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install curl -y
sudo curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ros/rosdistro/master/ros.key \
  -o /usr/share/keyrings/ros-archive-keyring.gpg

ðŸ”¹ STEP 4: Install ROS 2 Humble (Recommended)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ros-humble-desktop -y


â³ This may take a few minutes.

ðŸ”¹ STEP 5: Source ROS automatically

Add this line to your .bashrc:

echo "source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash" >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc

ðŸ”¹ STEP 6: Install build tools
sudo apt install python3-colcon-common-extensions -y

ðŸ”¹ STEP 7: Test ROS 2 installation ðŸŽ‰

Open two terminals.

Terminal 1:
ros2 run demo_nodes_cpp talker

Terminal 2:
ros2 run demo_nodes_py listener
